"```sql\nSELECT COUNT(*)\nFROM posts\nJOIN users ON posts.OwnerUserId = users.Id\nWHERE users.DisplayName = 'csgillespie' AND posts.ParentId IS NULL;\n```\n\nThis SQL query counts the number of root posts (posts with `ParentId` as NULL) owned by the user with the display name \"csgillespie\". It joins the `posts` and `users` tables using the `OwnerUserId` and `Id` columns, respectively, to filter posts by the specified user."